<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 3:11PM PDT  by NWS Reno</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of the North Valleys
through 400 PM PDT...
At 308 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sun Valley moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Torrential rainfall and winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Heavy rain could cause localized
flooding and ponding of water on roadways.
Locations impacted include...
Reno, Sparks, Wingfield Springs, Spanish Springs, Golden Valley,
Lemmon Valley, Lemmon Valley-Golden Valley, Nws Reno, Spanish Springs
Airport and Sun Valley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
